Project  O
title:  O
HUMIDITY  O
SENSING  O
USING  O
MICRROCONTRROLLER  O

College  O
Project  O
Team  O
Size:  O
4  O
members.  O

Project  O
Description:  O
The  O
aim  O
of  O
this  O
project  O
is  O
to  O
use  O
control  O
engineering  O
principles  O
and  O
concepts  O
to  O
provide  O
a  O
microcontroller  O
based  O
soil  O
moisture  O
sensing  O
system  O
In  O
crop  O
production  O
a  O
healthy  O
water  O
balance  O
is  O
essential  O
for  O
high  O
quality  O
yields..  O
Under-watered  O
crops  O
suffer  O
from  O
nutrient  O
deficiencies  O
while  O
over-watered  O
plants  O
are  O
more  O
susceptible  O
to  O
diseases  O
pressure  O
and  O
can  O
in  O
some  O
cases  O
lead  O
to  O
root  O
death  O
through  O
suffocation..  O
The  O
system  O
will  O
help  O
in  O
saving  O
money  O
and  O
water  O
and  O
at  O
the  O
same  O
time  O
increasing  O
crops  O
production..  O
The  O
automated  O
irrigation  O
system  O
is  O
controlled  O
using  O
ATmega16  O
micro  O
controller..  O
The  O
system  O
is  O
programmed  O
via  O
the  O
microcontroller  O
to  O
give  O
interrupt  O
signal  O
to  O
the  O
sensing  O
system  O
(sensor,  O
GSM  O
etc..)  O
depending  O
on  O
the  O
soil  O
moisture  O
levels..  O
The  O
soil  O
moisture/humidity  O
levels  O
are  O
checked  O
using  O
soil  O
moisture  O
sensor  O
Whenever  O
there  O
is  O
a  O
change  O
in  O
moisture/humidity  O
in  O
the  O
soil  O
this  O
sensor  O
senses  O
the  O
change  O
and  O
gives  O
an  O
interrupt  O
signal  O
to  O
the  O
micro-controller  O
and  O
thus  O
the  O
GSM  O
system  O
is  O
activated  O
or  O
deactivated.  O

global  O
image  O
semantics  O
into  O
account..  O

to  O
